   364	
   365	Example showing how to render a view from a template. Note that we are using `ModelAndView` class for setting the object and name/location of template. 
   366	
   367	First of all we define a class which handles and renders output depending on template engine used. In this case [FreeMarker](http://freemarker.incubator.apache.org/).
   368	
   369	
   370	```java
   371	public class FreeMarkerTemplateEngine extends TemplateEngine {
   372	
   373	    private Configuration configuration;
   374	
   375	    protected FreeMarkerTemplateEngine() {
   376	        this.configuration = createFreemarkerConfiguration();
   377	    }
   378	
   379	    @Override
   380	    public String render(ModelAndView modelAndView) {
   381	        try {
   382	            StringWriter stringWriter = new StringWriter();
   383	
   384	            Template template = configuration.getTemplate(modelAndView.getViewName());
   385	            template.process(modelAndView.getModel(), stringWriter);
   386	
   387	            return stringWriter.toString();
   388	        } catch (IOException e) {
   389	            throw new IllegalArgumentException(e);
   390	        } catch (TemplateException e) {
   391	            throw new IllegalArgumentException(e);
   392	        }
   393	    }
   394	
   395	    private Configuration createFreemarkerConfiguration() {
   396	        Configuration retVal = new Configuration();
   397	        retVal.setClassForTemplateLoading(FreeMarkerTemplateEngine.class, "freemarker");
   398	        return retVal;
   399	    }
   400	}
   401	```
   402	
   403	Then we can use it to generate our content. Note how we are setting model data and view name. Because we are using FreeMarker, in this case a `Map` and the name of the template is required:
   404	
   405	```java
   406	public class FreeMarkerExample {
   407	
   408	    public static void main(String args[]) {
   409	
   410	        get("/hello", (request, response) -> {
   411	            Map<String, Object> attributes = new HashMap<>();
   412	            attributes.put("message", "Hello FreeMarker World");
   413	
   414	            // The hello.ftl file is located in directory:
   415	            // src/test/resources/spark/examples/templateview/freemarker
   416	            return modelAndView(attributes, "hello.ftl");
   417	        }, new FreeMarkerTemplateEngine());
   418	    }
   419	}
   420	```
